As far as lore and story goes, I gotta say that I love Noxus. The whole badass military deal and all the ongoing stories with the internal politics with Swain's rise to power, the old Noxus supporters and aristocrats, and Riven and her reformists. It's a pretty exciting story.

From a theme perspective, Shadow Isles wins hands down. The whole spooky scary vibe, the endless legion of undead, the invasions and epic clashes of the Harrowing, are all just awesome. I also really like how there is this huge aura of mystery around it, with only bits and pieces of what goes on in the Shadow Isles and what it is like being released at a time. There has been a ton of theories and investigating into all the little details, and it's just exciting to wonder how close you got to the truth.
